exit:
NAME
	exit
SYNOPSIS
	Exits the program
DESCRIPTION
	The exit command is used to exit the program.
OPTIONS
	None.
ARGUMENTS
	None.
EXAMPLES
	To exit the program:
		exit
pwd:
NAME
	pwd
SYNOPSIS
	Prints current working directory
DESCRIPTION
	pwd will print the current working directory.
	A '$' indicates that the current working directory is within the vault.
	A '~' or '/' indicates that the current directory is a system path.
	'~' indicates that the current directory is relative to the vault root.
OPTIONS
	None.
ARGUMENTS
	None.
EXAMPLES
	To find current directory:
		pwd
sudo:
NAME
	sudo
SYNOPSIS
	Runs command with authenticated access
DESCRIPTION
	The following command runs with elevated privilege
OPTIONS
	None.
ARGUMENTS
	the command and its arguments
EXAMPLES
	change password:
		sudo set --password
help:
NAME
	help
SYNOPSIS
	Prints a help screen
DESCRIPTION
	Prints a list of commands that can be run
OPTIONS
	None.
ARGUMENTS
	None.
EXAMPLES
	To print help
		help
man:
NAME
	man
SYNOPSIS
	Prints manual page for the command
DESCRIPTION
	Well well well, you used man on man...
	which means you must already know how to use man
	which is just a waste for everyone involved
OPTIONS
	None.
ARGUMENTS
	the command to view man page of
EXAMPLES
	To see this page (super useful right?)
		man man
